			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">techtonik wrote:
&gt; Full URLs are not autolinked.

I'm not exactly sure what you mean by autolinked.  Full URLs are made
into clickable links on codereview.chromium.org if you put a space
between "BUG=" and the URL (for an example, see
http://codereview.chromium.org/4137001).  It would be nice to fix this
so that the space is not needed.

&gt; I've landed a patch that adds link to upstream issue to code review
&gt; tools. It can be seen at http://codereview.appspot.com/2790041/ and
&gt; demo at http://codereview-keydown.appspot.com/1/

I don't see why you want to put the bug number into Rietveld's side
panel.  We want the bug number to be included in the commit message.
